The federal government has approved the re-instatement of Professor Suleiman Bogoro as the executive secretary of the Tertiary Education Trust Fund (TETFund). According to a statement by the ministry of education and signed by the deputy director of information, Mr Ben Bem Goong, Bogoro’s appointment was directed by the minister of education, Mallam Adamu Adamu, and is with immediate effect. “The re-instatement of Prof. Bogoro is with immediate effect, with the same terms and conditions as it were in his previous appointment and as stipulated in the TETFund staff conditions of service,” it said. Prof Suleiman Bogoro was the executive secretary of TETFund between April 2014 and February 2016. At the time of his first appointment as the TETFund chief executive, he was still a lecturer at  Abubakar Tafawa Balewa University (ATBU), Bauchi State. The new TETFund boss was born in Bogoro, in Bogoro local government area of Bauchi State about 59 years ago. After his primary, secondary and tertiary education, he started his teaching profession as an Agric Science teacher at Oroke High School, Akungba Akoko, Ondo State, in 1981. Between 2005 and 2007, he became the chairman, Governing Council, Federal Polytechnic, Nekede, Owerri, Imo State, and a member of Nigeria Board for Technical Education (NBTE) committee. As an NBTE committee member, he was part of the team charged with the responsibility of fashioning out modalities for the removal of GL 14 ceiling for Higher National Diploma (HND) holders in Nigeria. He has also served as: executive board member, Gymnastics Federation of Nigeria (2001-2005); member, Board of Directors, Bauchi State Water Board (1994-1995); National Consultant/Team leader, UNDP Fourth Country Programme for Nigeria, 1992-96, and Consultant for the Federal Ministry of Labour & Productivity on Job Creation and Poverty Reduction Action Plan of Nigeria’s NEEDS/SEEDS programme, Bauchi/Gombe States (2004), among others.